last_episode_to_air.name: Garage Sale
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Carson family holds a garage sale during which Cory, Chrissy, Mama, and Papa race to make the most money and decide where they go for their next trip.

name: Go! Go! Cory Carson
overview: Beep, beep -- go, go! Buckle up for fun and adventure with adorable kid car Cory Carson as he explores the winding roads of Bumperton Hills.

episodes.name: Cory's First Day
episodes.overview: Cory's got big plans for his first day at Motorssori School. First on the agenda? Making friends. But it all feels a bit overwhelming.

episodes.name: Chrissy's Best Friend
episodes.overview: Cory's little sister has a new friend: a shiny red balloon named Loony. But for big brother Cory, keeping Loony safe is a full-time job.

episodes.name: Garbage Day
episodes.overview: Cory's thrilled when his favorite trash truck makes him a "Junior Garbage Apprentice" for the day. He's making the rounds -- and learning a lot!

episodes.name: Firehouse
episodes.overview: A tour of the firehouse led by Freddie's mom sounds exciting until a real-life emergency -- and Cory's behavior -- puts everyone at risk.

episodes.name: Oil Spill
episodes.overview: Mama and Papa are going on a date, so Cory and Chrissy have a babysitter. But Cory's convinced he's a big kid who doesn't really need one.

episodes.name: Sleepover
episodes.overview: Cory can't wait to spend the night at Kimmy and Timmy's house. But everything’s different when he gets there, and it doesn't feel like home.

episodes.name: Speed Limits
episodes.overview: When fun-loving Cory takes a turn as class safety monitor, he gets rid of all the rules -- only to realize that they're there for a reason.

episodes.name: Copy Car
episodes.overview: Little sister Chrissy wants to copy everything Cory does — and it's getting annoying! But sometimes copying someone is the best way to learn.

episodes.name: Happy Anniversary
episodes.overview: It's an afternoon full of surprises when Cory and Chrissy pitch in to help a stressed-out Mama make Papa a special anniversary dinner.

episodes.name: Mike's Carcade
episodes.overview: Cory's training so hard to win the upcoming Go! Go! Dance Party contest that he takes all the fun out of it for Freddie, his frustrated dance partner.

episodes.name: Flat Tire
episodes.overview: Cory gets a flat tire while practicing bumper ball with his friends — and the big game's just hours away! Can Dr. Wiperglass get him patched up to play?

episodes.name: Cory's New Bedroom
episodes.overview: To escape a clingy Chrissy, Cory asks his parents for his own room. But when he finally gets one, something doesn't feel quite right.

episodes.name: Grandpa's Treasure
episodes.overview: Special clues are everywhere when Mama and Papa take Cory and Chrissy on a treasure hunt to remember their grandfather on his birthday.

episodes.name: Ice Cream Truck
episodes.overview: A boiling-hot day in Bumperton Hills has everyone feeling overheated. Cue the sweet song of an ice cream truck ... if Cory and his friends can find it.

episodes.name: Cops & Robbers
episodes.overview: When little sister Chrissy steals something from the store while playing a game, Cory tries to be a good big brother by taking the blame himself.

episodes.name: Superhero School
episodes.overview: Cory creates a superpowered lesson plan for Chrissy when she wants to be a hero in their pretend play — and she’s learning to form sentences, too!

episodes.name: Bored Games
episodes.overview: When the Wi-Fi goes wacky while the Carsons are watching a movie, everyone’s imaginations go wild to act out the film and finish the ending.

episodes.name: Show and Tell
episodes.overview: Cory thinks none of his stuff is cool enough to follow up the best show-and-tell of all time. Will he find the perfect thing to bring in for his turn?

episodes.name: Teen Monster Truck
episodes.overview: Cory sneaks away to watch a scary movie with friends, but he regrets it when he starts getting spooked by bedroom shadows and noises in the night.

episodes.name: Karen
episodes.overview: Technically, she’s just a rock. But Karen is also Cory’s best friend. So when she goes missing, Cory is determined to search everywhere for her.

episodes.name: Near All-Nighter
episodes.overview: Midnight is way past bedtime, but Cory and Freddie are trying their best to stay up and catch the New Year’s Eve disco ball drop.

episodes.name: Winifred Wings
episodes.overview: Cory and Chrissy meet a kid plane named Winnie and help their new friend get over her nerves so she can fly high at an air show.

episodes.name: Substitute Teacher
episodes.overview: Cory and his classmates go crazy for ice cream when their substitute teacher, Eileen Ice Cream Truck, gives cones out after every lesson.

episodes.name: Spoiler Alert
episodes.overview: After seeing his hero Nitro Nicky with her super-cool spoiler, Cory wants one for himself. But will his oversized addition actually cramp his style?

episodes.name: Cory Loses a Tooth
episodes.overview: When Cory loses his first tooth, he thinks he’s falling apart and starts giving away all of his toys to Chrissy.

episodes.name: Trashy Romance
episodes.overview: Cory and Freddie do their best to help their garbage truck friend Gary get ready for a fancy dinner date with Sheryl Steamroller.

episodes.name: School Project
episodes.overview: Cory’s mom helps him build a fancy castle for a school project. But Cory’s simpler design might already do the trick!

episodes.name: Moby Fishy Face
episodes.overview: Chrissy brings home a fishy friend who was supposed to stay in the ocean, so Cory tries to hide it from their parents before it gets too big.

episodes.name: Fishaway Day
episodes.overview: During his first outing on the seas at Fishaway Day Camp, Cory learns that he doesn't need to catch a fish to have an awesome time.

episodes.name: New Kid
episodes.overview: A nervous new addition arrives in the classroom, and Cory's job as a first-day buddy is to make sure his new pal is having fun.

episodes.name: Strictly Spoiled
episodes.overview: Cory and Chrissy love getting spoiled by their overly-generous grandparents who allow ice cream for breakfast.

episodes.name: The Shimmering Poppygold
episodes.overview: Cory and the rest of the Hub Scouts try to slow down, look around and catch the beautiful bloom of a very rare flower.

episodes.name: Cory's Voice
episodes.overview: Cory lost his voice and his tummy's rumbling; he tries to send signals to his family to let them know what snack he's been craving.

episodes.name: Flying a Kite
episodes.overview: On a family picnic, Cory and his parents show little sister Chrissy the best ways to fly a kite and keep it floating.

episodes.name: The Big Nap
episodes.overview: When Chrissy's beloved blanket goes missing, Cory puts on his detective hat to track it down.

episodes.name: Junior Build
episodes.overview: On a construction crew, everyone has a job to do; Cory and friends have a busy day learning about the tasks at a building site.

episodes.name: The Library
episodes.overview: With his very first library card, Cory's ready to read even more, but he might have a hard time keeping track of all the books he's checked out.

episodes.name: Flight School
episodes.overview: Cory shares his flying fears with friend Winnie before taking off on a flight of his own.

episodes.name: Pet Plant
episodes.overview: Cory's friend Freddie takes great care of his new pet plant, only to discover that too much attention isn't always good for it.

episodes.name: Birthday Surprise
episodes.overview: Cory wants to surprise Mama for her birthday; when things don't go according to plan, the family must learn to make the best of it.

episodes.name: Opposite Day
episodes.overview: Cory convinces Chrissy that it's Opposite Day, and soon he has the entire town getting turned upside down.

episodes.name: Best Best Friend
episodes.overview: Halle and Freddie compete to be Cory's "best" best friend to see who will take his extra ticket to the Backstreet Buses show.

episodes.name: Coach Cory
episodes.overview: Cory's competitive spirit gets the best of him while calling the shots as the coach of Chrissy's soccer team.

episodes.name: Cory and the Tuba
episodes.overview: The Carson family adjusts to a new loud life when Cory starts learning to play the tuba and won't stop practicing.

episodes.name: Recess
episodes.overview: Cory, Freddie and Halle team up to face off with the rest of their class during a game of capture the flag at recess.

episodes.name: Bumper Bowling
episodes.overview: When the Carson family goes to a bowling alley, Cory decides to bowl without using bumpers.

episodes.name: Ball on the Roof
episodes.overview: After their ball gets stuck on the roof, Cory and pals realize they'll need teamwork to get it back.

episodes.name: Changing Lanes
episodes.overview: Chrissy and Cory trade places with their parents and take care of grownup stuff for the day — all while Mama and Papa act like the kids.

episodes.name: Birthday Buddy
episodes.overview: Cory tries to hop between two different birthday parties, but he soon starts spinning out of control at both.

episodes.name: Blustery Beach Day
episodes.overview: The Carson family has fun at the beach even while trying to get a handle on the wild and windy weather.

episodes.name: Mary Mailtruck
episodes.overview: Cory and Chrissy help Mary Mailtruck with her deliveries so they can get Chrissy's present at the post office.

episodes.name: Ice Skating
episodes.overview: Freddie heads to the ice rink for the first time, so Cory shows off some cool moves to keep his friend from being scared.

episodes.name: Harry Hoodini
episodes.overview: A magician's flashy fenders are no match for skeptical Frannie, who tries to prove the power of his magic is all a trick.

episodes.name: Baby Unicar Fever
episodes.overview: Cory tries to kick his cold to the curb so he can catch the premiere of the latest "Baby Unicar" movie.

episodes.name: Yipita Cartínez
episodes.overview: Cory and pals explore fun ways to play with their new friend who only speaks Spanish, even if they only understand some of the same words.

episodes.name: Itchy Sweater
episodes.overview: Cory tries really hard not to think about how itchy he is while wearing one of Nana's famous knitted sweaters.

episodes.name: Stuck on the Tracks
episodes.overview: The town helps Mr. Coaltrain get unstuck from the tracks but keeps interrupting his story about chasing down a bandit.

episodes.name: Freddie the Houseguest
episodes.overview: When Freddie stays at Cory's for an extended sleep-over, the friends find out that a whole week together may be too much.

episodes.name: Helpful Halle
episodes.overview: Halle's new fame goes to her head after she uses her helicopter skills to save a balloon on the loose.

episodes.name: Cuzzy Carson
episodes.overview: Cory worries he's gotten too big to play with his favorite cousin, Cassie, when she drives in for a visit.

episodes.name: Bedtime Story
episodes.overview: Mama, Papa and Cory all try to top each other's bedtime stories while hoping Chrissy can finally fall asleep.

episodes.name: School Play
episodes.overview: Cory loses the lead role in the school play to Ping but still helps his shy classmate shine in the spotlight.

episodes.name: Garage Sale
episodes.overview: The Carson family holds a garage sale during which Cory, Chrissy, Mama, and Papa race to make the most money and decide where they go for their next trip.
